revision.text:
{{Use Australian English|date=April 2018}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}
The '''Aboriginal Heritage Act 2006 of Victoria''', Australia was enacted "to provide for the protection of Aboriginal cultural heritage in Victoria." It established [[Registered Aboriginal Party|Registered Aboriginal Parties]] to act as the "primary guardians, keepers and knowledge holders of Aboriginal cultural heritage." They protect and manage the Aboriginal cultural heritage in Victoria, Australia.<ref name="DPC RAP">{{cite web | url=http://www.dpc.vic.gov.au/index.php/aboriginal-affairs/registered-aboriginal-parties | title=Registered Aboriginal Parties | publisher=State of Victoria, Department of Premier and Cabinet | accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/legis/vic/consol_act/aha2006164/s1.html | title=Aboriginal Heritage Act 2006: Purpose | publisher=Australasian Legal Information Institute | accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref>

==Objectives==

The objectives, stated in Section 3 of the Act, are:<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/legis/vic/consol_act/aha2006164/s3.html | title=Aboriginal Heritage Act 2006: Objectives | publisher=Australasian Legal Information Institute | accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref>
* "to recognise, protect and conserve [[Aboriginal Australians|Aboriginal]] cultural heritage in Victoria in ways that are based on respect for Aboriginal knowledge and cultural and traditional practices;
* to recognise Aboriginal people as the primary guardians, keepers and knowledge holders of Aboriginal cultural heritage;
* to accord appropriate status to Aboriginal people with traditional or familial links with Aboriginal cultural heritage in protecting that heritage;
* to promote the management of Aboriginal cultural heritage as an integral part of land and natural resource 
* to promote public awareness and understanding of Aboriginal cultural heritage in Victoria;
* to establish an [[Victorian Aboriginal Heritage Register|Aboriginal cultural heritage register]] to record Aboriginal cultural 
* to establish processes for the timely and efficient assessment of activities that have the potential to harm Aboriginal cultural heritage;
* to promote the use of agreements that provide for the management and protection of Aboriginal cultural heritage;
* to establish mechanisms that enable the resolution of disputes relating to the protection of Aboriginal cultural heritage;
* to provide appropriate sanctions and penalties to prevent harm to Aboriginal cultural heritage."

